  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 1-4.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The ordinance on the lamps contained in the first three verses is repeated from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 27:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The oil to be used for the lamps was to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "pure oil olive",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that is, oil made of picked berries, without any intermixture of dust or twigs; and it was to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "beaten",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " instead of \"pressed,\" because when the berries were crushed in the olive-press, small portions of them became mixed with and discoloured the oil, which ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "was",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", therefore, less pure than when the fruit was simply beaten and then left to drain. The lamps were to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "burn continually",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "is",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", from evening to morning every night. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Without the vail of the testimony, in the tabernacle of the congregation;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that is, in the holy place, as distinct from the holy of holies. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Aaron",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", either personally or by his sons (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 27:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), was to dress the lamps every morning, and light them every evening (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 30:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The lamps were upon the seven-branched candlestick, which is called the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "pure candlestick",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", because made of gold. The light of the seven-branched candlestick symbolized the enlightening power of the Holy Spirit, which should illumine God's Church (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 4:2-6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 1:12, 20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Leviticus 24:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
